<paragraph id="8BC6A742FF89FF92F1CDFC25ED63FBB2" blockId="12.[166,1225,911,1258]" pageId="12" pageNumber="399">
С o m p a r a t i v e n o t e s. 
<taxonomicName id="4C79DCC1FF89FF92F300FC3AECF3FC52" authorityName="Stary" authorityYear="1971" box="[534,707,911,937]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Trioxys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="399" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tanaceticola">
<emphasis id="B90D7B50FF89FF92F300FC3AECF3FC52" box="[534,707,911,937]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="399">T. tanaceticola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="1342BBC7FF89FF92F3C5FC25ED2FFC51" box="[723,799,911,938]" captionStart="Fig 11" captionStartId="11.[174,204,1720,1742]" captionTargetBox="[292,1115,1159,1704]" captionTargetId="figure-395@11.[280,1127,1150,1717]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig 11. Trioxys tanaceticola, ♀: 1 — forewing; 2 — propodeum; 3 — petiole; 4 — ovipositor sheath and prongs; 5 — apex of ovipositor sheath; 6 — apex of prong with clawlike bristles. Рис. 11. Trioxys tanaceticola,♀: 1 — переднее крыло; 2 — проподеум; 3 — стебелёк;4 — створки яйцеклада и пронги; 5 — вершина створок яйцеклада; 6 — вершина пронг с коготковидными щетинками." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449145" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6449145/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="399">fig. 11</figureCitation>
) is similar to European species 
<taxonomicName id="4C79DCC1FF89FF92F58CFC3AEC38FC32" authority="Mackauer, 1960" authorityName="Mackauer" authorityYear="1960" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Trioxys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="399" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lambersi">
<emphasis id="B90D7B50FF89FF92F58CFC3AEF74FC32" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="399">Trioxys lambersi</emphasis>
Mackauer, 1960
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFE8DAB3FF89FF92F30EFC05ECE2FC31" author="Davidian, E. M." box="[536,722,943,970]" pageId="12" pageNumber="399" refId="ref7221" refString="Davidian, E. M. Fam. Aphidiidae / Ed. A. S. Leley // Keys to the insects of Russian Far East. Vol. IV. Neuropteromorpha, Mecoptera, Hymenoptera. Pt. 5. - Vladivostok: Dal'nauka, 2007. - P. 192 - 254. - Russian: Davidьiн I. М. Сiм. Aphidiidae // Opрidiлitiль нaсikoмыk Daльнigo Voсtoka Рoссii. T. 4. Сitcatokрылoobрazныi, сkoрpioннitы, piрipoнcatokрылыi. C. 5." type="book" year="2007">Davidian, 2007</bibRefCitation>
), and differs by: 1) 11-segmented antenna; 2) more prominent spiracular tubercules; 3) apical part of ovipositor sheath is shorter; 4) clawlike bristles on prongs apexes is shorter. Moreover, it should be noted, that apex of ovipositor sheath of 
<taxonomicName id="4C79DCC1FF89FF92F081FBBAEC73FBD2" authorityName="Stary" authorityYear="1971" box="[407,579,1039,1065]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Trioxys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="399" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tanaceticola">
<emphasis id="B90D7B50FF89FF92F081FBBAEC73FBD2" box="[407,579,1039,1065]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="399">T. tanaceticola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
bearing three conical spines (
<figureCitation id="1342BBC7FF89FF92F2B7FBA5EDDCFBD2" box="[929,1004,1039,1065]" captionStart="Fig 11" captionStartId="11.[174,204,1720,1742]" captionTargetBox="[292,1115,1159,1704]" captionTargetId="figure-395@11.[280,1127,1150,1717]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig 11. Trioxys tanaceticola, ♀: 1 — forewing; 2 — propodeum; 3 — petiole; 4 — ovipositor sheath and prongs; 5 — apex of ovipositor sheath; 6 — apex of prong with clawlike bristles. Рис. 11. Trioxys tanaceticola,♀: 1 — переднее крыло; 2 — проподеум; 3 — стебелёк;4 — створки яйцеклада и пронги; 5 — вершина створок яйцеклада; 6 — вершина пронг с коготковидными щетинками." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449145" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6449145/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="399">fig. 11</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="1342BBC7FF89FF92F2EEFBBAEA36FBD1" box="[1016,1030,1040,1066]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[171,204,1732,1754]" captionTargetBox="[321,1089,843,1706]" captionTargetId="figure-5@5.[311,1097,833,1721]" captionText="Fig. 5. Ephedrus cerasicola, ♀ (1–6), E.plagiator, ♀ (7, 10–12), E. niger, ♀ (8, 9): 1, 7 — antenna; 2, 8 — mesonotum; 3, 9 — forewing; 4, 10 — propodeum; 5, 11 — petiole; 6, 12 — ovipositor sheath. Рис. 5. Ephedrus cerasicola, ♀ (1–6), E. plagiator, ♀ (7, 10–12), E. niger, ♀ (8, 9): 1, 7 — усик; 2, 8 — среднеспинка; 3, 9 — переднее крыло; 4, 10 — проподеум; 5, 11 — стебелёк; 6, 12 — створки яйцеклада." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6467462" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6467462/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="399">
<emphasis id="B90D7B50FF89FF92F2EEFBBAEA36FBD1" box="[1016,1030,1040,1066]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="399">5</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
); this diagnostic character could be helpful in 
<taxonomicName id="4C79DCC1FF89FF92F0EBFB9AEC98FBB2" authorityName="Stary" authorityYear="1971" box="[509,680,1071,1097]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Trioxys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="399" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tanaceticola">
<emphasis id="B90D7B50FF89FF92F0EBFB9AEC98FBB2" box="[509,680,1071,1097]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="399">T. tanaceticola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
identification.
</paragraph>
